obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (48864)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48864&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1)This Act may be called the ^1*** Explosives Act, 1884; and`
  line
  line `(2)Local extent.--It extends to whole India ^2**`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-3-1983).`
  line
  line `2. The words and letter "except Part B States" omitted by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (48865)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Commencement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48865&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act shall come into force on such day,^1 as the Central Government, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoints.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st July, 1887--see Gazette of India, 1887, Pt. I, p. 307`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) rep. by Act 12 of 1891, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (48866)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48866&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `[Repeal of portions of Act 12 of 1875.] Rep. by the Indian Ports Act, 1889 (10 of 1889), s. 2`
  line `and the Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (48867)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 4. for section 4 (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48867&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `^1[4. Definitions.--In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "aircraft" means any machine which can derive support in the atmosphere from the reactions`
  line `of the air, other than the reactions of the air against the earth's surface, and includes balloons, whether`
  line `fixed or free, airships, kites, gliders and flying machines;`
  line
  line `(b) "carriage" includes any carriage, wagon, cart, truck, vehicle or other means of conveying`
  line `goods or passengers by land, in whatever manner the same may be propelled,`
  line
  line `(c) "District Magistrate", in relation to any area for which a Commissioner of Police has been`
  line `appointed, means the Commissioner of Police thereof and includes--`
  line
  line `(a) any such Deputy Commissioner of Police, exercising jurisdiction over the whole or any`
  line `part of such area, as may be specified by the State Government in this behalf in relation to such`
  line `area or part: and`
  line
  line `(b) an Additional District Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(d) "explosive" means gunpowder, nitoglycerine, nitroglycol, gun-cotton, di-nitro-toluene,`
  line `tri-nitro-toluene, picric acid, di-nitro-phenol, tri-nitro-resorcinol (styphnic acid), cyclo-trime-`
  line `thylene-trinitramine, penta-erythritol-tetranitrate, tetryl, nitro-guanidine, lead azide, lead`
  line `styphynate, fulminate of mercury or any other metal, diazo -di-nitro-phenol, coloured fires`
  line `or any other substance whether a single chemical compound or a mixture of substances,`
  line `whether solid or liquid or gaseous used or manufactured with a view to produce a practical`
  line `effect by explosion or pyrotechnic effect; and includes fog-signals, fireworks, fuses,`
  line `rockets, percussion-caps, detonators, cartidgcs, ammunition of all descriptions and every`
  line `adaptation or preparation of an explosive as defined in this clause;`
  line
  line `(e) "export" means taking out of India to a place outside India by land, sea or air;`
  line
  line `(f) "import" means to bring into India from a place outside India by land, sea or air;`
  line
  line `(g) "master",--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to any vessel or aircraft means any person, other than a pilot, harbour`
  line `master, assistant harbour master or berthing master, having for the time bein g the`
  line `charge or control of such vessel or aircraft, as the ease may be; and`
  line
  line `(b) in relation to any boat belonging to a ship, means the master of that ship;`
  line
  line `(h) "manufacture" in relation to an explosive includes the process of--`
  line
  line `(1) dividing the explosive into its component parts or otherwise breaking up or`
  line `unmaking the explosive, or making fit for use any damaged explosive; and`
  line
  line `(2) re-making, altering or repairing the explosive;`
  line
  line `(i) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "vessel" includes any ship, boat, sailing vessel, or other description of vessel used in`
  line `navigation whether propelled by oars or otherwise and anything made for the conveyance,`
  line `mainly by water, of human beings or of goods and a caisson.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (48868)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to make rules as to licensing of the manufacture, possession, use, sale, transport and import and Export of explosives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48868&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, for any part`
  line `of ^1[India],^2*** make rules consistent with this Act to regulate or prohibit, except under and in`
  line `accordance with the conditions of a licence granted as provided by those rules, the manuf acture,`
  line `possession, use, sale. ^3[transport, import and export] of explosives, or any specified class of`
  line explosives.
  line
  line `(2) Rules under this section may provide for all or any of the following, among other matters, that is`
  line `to say:--`
  line
  line `(a) the authority by which licenses may be granted;`
  line
  line `(b) the fees to be charged for licenses, and the other sums (if any) to be paid for expenses by`
  line `applicants for licenses:`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which applications for licenses must be made, and the matters to be specified`
  line `in such applications:`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which, and the conditions on and subject to which, licenses must be`
  line granted;
  line
  line `( e) the period for which licenses are to remain in force; ^4***`
  line
  line `^5[(ee) the authority to which appeals may be preferred under section 6F, the procedure to`
  line `be followed by such authority and the period within which appeals shall be preferred, the fees to be paid in respect of such appeals and the circumstances under which such fees may be`
  line `refunded:`
  line
  line `(eea)the total quantity of explosives that a licensee can purchase in a given period of time;`
  line
  line `(eeb) the fees to be charged by the Chief Controller of Explosives or any officer authorised by`
  line `him in this behalf, for services rendered in connection with the manufacture, transport, import or`
  line `export of explosives;]`
  line
  line `(f) the exemption absolutely or subject to conditions of any explosives ^6[or any person or class of`
  line `persons] from the operation of the rules.`
  line
  line `^7* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and Schedule, for "Part A States and Part C States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line
  line `2. The words and "each Local Government, with the previous sanction of the Governor, General in Council, may for any part of`
  line `the territories wider its administration" omitted by the A.O. 1937.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 5, for "transport and importation" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `4. The word "and" omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `5.Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `7. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (48869)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Persons already in business in respect of certain explosives to carry on such business without licence for a certain period.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48869&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `Notwithstanding anything in section 5 or in the rules made`
  line `thereunder where, immediately before the commencement of the Indian Explosives (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1978 (32 of 1978), any person was carrying on the business of manufacture, sale, transport,`
  line `import or export of any explosive (for which no licence was required under this Act before its`
  line `amendment by the Indian Explosives (Amendment) Act, 1978, then, such person shall be entitled`
  line `to continue to carry on such business without licence in respect of such explosive`
  line `(a) for a period of three months from the date of such commencement; or`
  line `(b) if before the expiry of the said period of three months, such person has made an application`
  line `for grant of licence under this Act for such business in such explosive, until the final disposal of his`
  line application,
  line `whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (48870)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power for Central Government to prohibit the manufacture, possession or importation of specially dangerous explosives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48870&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything in the rules under the last foregoing`
  line `section, the Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) prohibit, either absolutely or subject to conditions, the manufacture, possession or`
  line `importation of any explosive which is of so dangerous a character that, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, it is expedient for the public safety to issue the notification. ^1***.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(2) The Customs Act, 1962 (52 of 1962) shall have effect in relation to any explosive with`
  line `regard to the importation of which a notification has been issued under this section and the vessel,`
  line `carriage or aircraft containing such explosive as that Act has in relation to any article the`
  line `importance of which is prohibited or regulated thereunder and the vessel, carriage or aircraft`
  line `containing such article.`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "and" and cl. (b) rep. by Act 10 of 1914, s. 3 and the Second Schedule.`
  line
  line `2. Clause (b) rep. by s. 3 and the Second Schedule, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 7, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-section (3) omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (48871)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 8
  title `Prohibition of manufacture, possession, sale or transport of explosives by young persons and certain other persons`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48871&sectionno=6A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Prohibition of manufacture, possession, sale or transport of explosives by young persons and`
  line `certain other persons.--Notwithstanding anything in the foregoing provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) no person,--`
  line
  line `(i) who has not completed the age of eighteen years, or`
  line
  line `(ii) who has been sentenced on conviction of any offence involving violence or moral`
  line `turpitude for a term not less than six months, at any time during a period of five years after the`
  line `expiration of the sentence, or`
  line
  line `(iii)who has been ordered to execute under Chapter VIII of the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) a bond for keeping the peace or for good`
  line `behaviour, at any time during the term of the bond., or`
  line
  line `(iv) whose licence under this Act has been cancelled, whether before Or after the`
  line `commencement of the Indian Explosives (Amendment) Act, 1978 (32 of 1978), for`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act or of the rules made thereunder, at any time`
  line `during a period of five years from the date of cancellation of such licence, shall,`
  line
  line `(1) manufacture, sell, .transport, import or export any explosive, or`
  line
  line `(2) possess any such explosive as the Central Government may, having regard to`
  line `the nature thereof, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `(b) no person shall sell, deliver or despatch any explosive to a person whom he knows`
  line `or has reason to believe at the time of such sale, delivery or despatch,--`
  line
  line `(i) to be prohibited under clause (a) to manufacture, sell, transport, import, export or possess`
  line `such explosive, or`
  line
  line `(ii) to be of unsound mind.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b:
  sectionId (48872)
  sectionNo 6B
  orderNo 9
  title `Grant of licences`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48872&sectionno=6B&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[6B. Grant of licences.--(1) Where a person makes an application for licence under`
  line `section 5, the authority prescribed in the rules made under that section for grant of licences`
  line `(hereinafter referred to in this Act as the licensing authority), after making such inquiry, if any,`
  line `as it may consider necessary, shall, subject to the other provisions of this Act, by order in writing`
  line `either grant the licence or refuse to grant the same.`
  line
  line `(2) The licensing authority shall grant a licence--`
  line
  line `(a) where it is required for the purpose of manufacture. of explosives if the licensing`
  line `authority is satisfied that the person by whom license is required--`
  line
  line `(i) possesses technical know-how and experience in the manufacture of explosives;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) has in his employment or undertakes to employ a person or persons possessing such`
  line `technical know-how and experience; or`
  line
  line `(b) where it is required for any other purpose, if the licensing authority is satisfied that the person`
  line `by whom licence is required has a good reason for obtaining the same.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c:
  sectionId (48873)
  sectionNo 6C
  orderNo 10
  title `Refusal of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48873&sectionno=6C&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[6C. Refusal of licences.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 6B, the licensing`
  line `authority shall refuse to grant a licence--`
  line
  line `(a) where such licence is required in respect of any prohibited explosive; or`
  line
  line `(b) where such licence is required by a person whom the licensing authority has reason to`
  line believe--
  line
  line `(i) to be prohibited by this Act or by any other law for the time being in force to`
  line
  line `manufacture, possess, sell, transport. import or export any explosive, or`
  line `(ii) to be of unsound mind, or`
  line
  line `(iii) to be for any reason unfit for a licence under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) where the licensing authority deems it necessary for the security of the public peace or for`
  line `public safety to refuse to grant such licence.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the licensing authority refuses to grant a licence to any person it shall record in`
  line `writing the reasons for such refusal and furnish to that person on demand a brief statement of the`
  line `same unless in any case the licensing authority is of opinion that it will not be in the public`
  line `interest to furnish such statement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_d:
  sectionId (48874)
  sectionNo 6D
  orderNo 11
  title `Licensing authority competent to impose conditions in addition to prescribed conditions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48874&sectionno=6D&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[6D. Licensing authority competent to impose conditions in addition to prescribed`
  line `conditions.--A licence granted under section 6B may contain in addition to prescribed`
  line `conditions such other conditions as may be considered necessary by the licensing authority in`
  line `any particular case.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_e:
  sectionId (48875)
  sectionNo 6E
  orderNo 12
  title `Variation, suspension and revocation of licences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48875&sectionno=6E&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[6E. Variation, suspension and revocation of licences.--(1) The licensing authority may vary the`
  line `conditions subject to which a licence has been granted except such of them as have been prescribed and`
  line `may for that purpose require the holder of licence by notice in writing to deliver-up the licence to it within`
  line `such time as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) The licensing authority may, on the application of the holder of a licence, also vary the conditions`
  line `of the licence except such of them as have been prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The licensing authority may, by order in writing, suspend a licence for such period as it thinks fit`
  line `or revoke a licence,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the licensing authority is satisfied that the holder of the licence is prohibited by this Act or`
  line `by any other law for the time being in force to manufacture, possess, sell, transport, import or export`
  line `any explosive, or is of unsound mind, or is for any reason unfit for a licence under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the licensing authority deems it necessary for the security of the public peace or for public`
  line `safety to suspend or revoke the licence; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the licence was obtained by the suppression of material information or on the basis of`
  line `wrong information provided by the holder of the licence or any other person on his behalf at the time`
  line `of applying for the licence; or`
  line
  line `(d) if any of the conditions of the licence has been contravened; or`
  line
  line `(e) if the holder of the licence has failed to comply with a notice under sub-section (1) requiring`
  line `him to deliver-up the licence.`
  line
  line `(4) The licensing authority may also revoke a licence on the application of the holder thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) where the licensing authority makes an order varying the conditions of a licence under`
  line `sub-section (1) or an order suspending or revoking a licence under sub-section (3), it shall record in`
  line `writing the reasons therefor and furnish to the holder of the licence on demand a brief statement of the`
  line `same unless in any case the licensing authority is of the opinion that it will not be in the public interest to`
  line `furnish such statement.`
  line
  line `(6) A court convicting the holder of a licence of any offence under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder may also suspend or revoke a licence:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the conviction is set aside on appeal or otherwise, the suspension or revocation shall`
  line `become void.`
  line
  line `(7) An order of suspension or revocation under sub-section (6) may also be made by an appellate`
  line `court or by the High Court when exercising its powers of revision.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government may, by order in the Official Gazette, suspend or revoke, or direct any`
  line `licensing authority to suspend or revoke, all or any licences granted under this .Act throughout India or`
  line `any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(9) On the suspension or revocation of a licence under this section the holder thereof shall without`
  line `delay surrender the licence to the authority by whom it has been suspended or revoked or to such other`
  line `authority as may be specified in this behalf in the order of suspension or revocation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_f:
  sectionId (48876)
  sectionNo 6F
  orderNo 13
  title Appeals
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48876&sectionno=6F&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_6_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[6F. Appeals.--(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the licensing authority refusing to grant a`
  line `licence or varying the conditions of a licence or by an order of the licensing authority suspending or revoking a licence may prefer an appeal against that order to such authority (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `appellate authority) and within such period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall lie against an order made by, or under the direction of, the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(2) No appeal shall be admitted if it is preferred after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period prescribed therefor if the`
  line `appellant satisfies the appellate authority that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within`
  line `that period.`
  line
  line `(3) The period prescribed for an appeal shall be computed in accordance with the provisions of the`
  line `Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), with respect to the computation of periods of limitation thereunder.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal under this section shall be made by a petition in writing and shall be`
  line `accompanied by a brief statement of the reasons for the order appealed agianst where such`
  line `statement has been furnished to the appellant and by such fee as may be prescribed .`
  line
  line `(5) In disposing of an appeal the appellate authority shall follow such procedure as may be`
  line `prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no appeal shall be disposed of unless the appellant has been given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(6) The order appealed against shall, unless the appellate authority conditionally or`
  line `unconditionally directs otherwise, be in force pending the disposal of the appeal against such order.`
  line
  line `(7) Every order of the appellate authority confirming, modifying or reversing the order appealed`
  line `against shall be final.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (48877)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make rules conferring powers of inspection, search, seizure, detention and removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48877&sectionno=7&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government ^1*** may make rules consistent with this Act authorising any`
  line `officer, either by name or in virtue of his office.--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter, inspect and examine ^2[any place, aircraft, carriage or vessel] in which an`
  line `explosive is being manufactured, possessed, used, sold, ^3[transported, imported or exported]`
  line `under a license granted under this Act, or in which he has reason to believe that an explosive has`
  line `been or is being manufactured, possessed, used, sold, ^3[transported, imported or exported] in`
  line `contravention of this Act or of the rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) to search for explosives therein;`
  line
  line `(c) to take samples of any explosive found therein on payment of the value thereof; and`
  line
  line `^4[(d) to seize, detain and remove any explosive or ingredient thereof found therein and, if`
  line `necessary, also destroy such explosive or ingredient.]`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the ^5[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)] relating to searches under`
  line `that Code shall, so far as the same are applicable, apply to searches by officers authorised by rules under`
  line `this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or the Local Government with the previous sanction of the Governor-General in Council" omitted by the A.O.`
  line 1937.
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 9, for "any place, carriage or vessel" (w.e.f. 2 -3-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "transported or imported" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure (10 of 1882)" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (48878)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 15
  title `Notice of accidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48878&sectionno=8&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Whenever there occurs in or about, or in connection with, any`
  line `place in which an explosive is manufactured, possessed or used, or ^2[any aircraft, carriage or vessel]`
  line `either conveying an explosive or on or from which an explosive is being loaded or unloaded, any`
  line `accident by explosion or by fire attended with loss of human life or serious injury to person or property, or of a description usually attended with such loss or injury, the occupier of the place, or`
  line `^3[the master of the aircraft or vessel], or the person in charge of the carriage, as the case may be, shall`
  line `^4[within such time and in such manner as may be by rule prescribed give notice thereof and of the`
  line `attendant loss of human life or personal injury, if any, to the ^5[Chief Controller of Explosives] and] to the`
  line `officer in charge of the nearest police-station.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 8 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by 18 of 1945, s. 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 10, for "any carriage or vessel" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 10, for "the master of vessel" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by 18 of 1945, s. 2, for "forthwith give notice thereof".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 10, for "Chief Inspector of Explosives in India" (w.e.f. 2 -3-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (48879)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 16
  title `Inquiry into accidents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48879&sectionno=9&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[9. Inquiry into accidents.--(1) Where any accident such as is referred to in section 8 occurs`
  line `in or about or in connection with ^1[any place, aircraft, carriage or vessel] under the control of any`
  line `of ^3[Armed Forces of the Union], an inquiry into the causes of the accident shall be held by the`
  line `naval, military, or air force authority concerned, and where any such accident occurs in any other`
  line `circumstances, the District Magistrate ^4* * *shall, in cases attended by loss of human life, or may,`
  line `in any other case, hold or direct a Magistrate subordinate to him to hold, such an Inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person holding an inquiry under this section shall have all the powers of a Magistrate in`
  line `holding an inquiry into an offence under the ^5[Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], and`
  line `may exercise such of the powers conferred on any officer by rules under section 7 as he may think it`
  line `necessary or expedient to exercise for the purposes of the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The person holding an inquiry under this section shall make a report to the Central Government`
  line `stating the causes of the accident and its circumstances.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may make rules--`
  line
  line `(a) to regulate the procedure at inquiries under this section;`
  line
  line `(b) to enable the ^6[Chief Controller of Explosives] to be present or represented at any such`
  line inquiry;
  line
  line `(c) to permit the ^6[Chief Controller of Explosives] or his representative to examine any`
  line `witnesses at the inquiry;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide that where the ^6[Chief Controller of Explosives] is not present or represented at`
  line `any such inquiry, a report of the proceedings thereof shall be sent to him;`
  line
  line `(e) to prescribe the manner in which and the time within which notices referred to in section 8`
  line `shall be given.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 18 of 1945, s. 3, for section 9.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 11, for "any place, carriage or vessel" (w.e.f. 2 -3-1983).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "the Indian Forces" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `4. The brackets and words "(or in a Presidency-town, the Commissioner of Police)" omitted by s. 11, ibid.`
  line
  line `(w.e.f. 2-31983).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "Chief Inspector of Explosives in India" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (48880)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 17
  title `Inquiry into more serious accidents`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48880&sectionno=9A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Inquiry into more serious accidents.--(1) The Central Government may, where it is of`
  line `opinion, whether or not it has received the report of an inquiry under section 9, that an inquiry or more`
  line `formal character should be held into the causes of an accident such as is referred to in section 8, appoint`
  line `the ^1[Chief Controller of Explosives] or any other competent person to hold such inquiry, and may also`
  line `appoint one or more persons possessing legal or special knowledge to act as assessors in such inquiry.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Central Government orders an inquiry under this section, it may also direct that any`
  line `inquiry under section 9 pending at the time shall be discontinued.`
  line
  line `(3) The person appointed to hold an inquiry under this section shall have all the powers of a Civil`
  line `Court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), for the purposes of enforcing the`
  line `attendance of witnesses and compelling the production of documents and material objects; and every person required by such person as aforesaid to furnish any information shall be deemed to be legally`
  line `bound so to do within the meaning of section 176 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1890).`
  line
  line `(4) Any person holding an inquiry under this section may exercise such of the powers conferred on`
  line `any officer by rules under section 7 as he may think it necessary or expedient to exercise for the purposes`
  line `of the inquiry.`
  line
  line `(5) The person holding an inquiry under this section shall make a report to the Central`
  line `Government stating the causes of the accident and its circumstances, and adding any observations`
  line `which he or any of the assessors may think fit to make; and the Central Government shall cause`
  line `every report so made to be published at such time and in such manner as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may make rules for regulating the procedure at inquiries under this`
  line section.]
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 18 of 1945, s. 3, for section 9.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for "Chief Inspector of Explosives in India" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (48970)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 18
  title `Punishment for certain offences`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 13.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48970&sectionno=9B&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[9B. Punishment for certain offences.--(1) Whoever, in contravention of rules made under section`
  line `5 or of the conditions of a licence granted under the said rules--`
  line
  line `(a) manufactures, imports or exports any explosive shall he punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line both;
  line
  line `(b) possesses, uses, sells or transports any explosive shall be punishable with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to three thousand rupees or with`
  line `both; and`
  line
  line `(c) in any other case, with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever in contravention of a notification issued under section 6 manufactures, possesses or`
  line `imports any explosive shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three`
  line `years or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees or with both; and in the case of`
  line `importation by water, the owner and master of the vessel or in the ease of importation by air, the`
  line `owner, and the master of the aircraft, in which the explosive is imported shall, in the absence of`
  line `reasonable excuse, each be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever,--`
  line
  line `(a) manufactures, sells, transports, imports, exports or possesses any explosive in contravention`
  line `of the provisions of clause (a) of section 6A; or`
  line
  line `(b) sells, delivers or despatches any explosive in contravention of the provisions of clause (b) of`
  line `that section, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years or`
  line `with fine or with both; or`
  line
  line `(c) in contravention of the provisions of section 8 fails to give notice of any accident shall be`
  line punishable,--
  line
  line `(i) with fine which may extend to five hundred rupees, or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the accident is attended by loss of human life, withimprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to three months or with fine or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_c:
  sectionId (48971)
  sectionNo 9C
  orderNo 19
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 13.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48971&sectionno=9C&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_9_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[9C. Offences by companies.--(1) Whenever an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, or was responsible`
  line `t6 the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment under this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge and`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be`
  line `deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate, and includes a firm or other association of`
  line `individuals; and`
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, Means a partner in the firm.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (48881)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 20
  title `Forfeiture of explosives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48881&sectionno=10&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When a person is convicted of an offence punishable under this Act,`
  line `or the rules made under this Act, the court before which he is convicted may direct that the explosive, or`
  line `ingredient of the explosive, or the substance (if any) in respect of which the offence has been committed,`
  line `or any part of that explosive, ingredient or substance, shall, with the receptacles containing the same, be`
  line forfeited.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (48882)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title `Distress of aircraft or vessel`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 14, for s. 11 (w.e.f.2 -3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48882&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Distress of aircraft or vessel.--Where the owner or Master of any aircraft or vessel is`
  line `adjudged under this Act to pay a fine for any offence committed with, or in relation to, that`
  line `aircraft or vessel, the. Court may, in addition to any power it may have for the purpose of`
  line `compelling payment of the fine, direct it to be levied by distress and sale of,--`
  line
  line `(a) the aircraft and its furniture or so much of the furniture, or`
  line
  line `(b) the vessel and the tackle, apparel and furniture of such vessel or so much of the tackle,`
  line `apparel and furniture thereof,`
  line
  line `as is necessary for the payment of the fine.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (48883)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Abetment and attempts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48883&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Whoever abets, within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860), the commission of an offence punishable under this Act, or the rules made under this Act, or`
  line `attempts to commit.. any such offence and in such attempt does any act towards the commission of the`
  line `same, shall be punished as if he had committed the offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (48884)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to arrest without warrant persons committing dangerous offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48884&sectionno=13&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Whoever is`
  line `found committing any act for which he is punishable under this Act or the rules under this Act, and`
  line `which tends to cause explosion or fire in or about any place where an explosive is manufactured or`
  line `stored, or any railway or port, or any carriage, ^1[aircraft or vessel], may be apprehended without a`
  line `warrant by a Police-officer, or by the occupier of, or the agent or servant of, or other person`
  line `authorised by the occupier of, that place, or by any agent or servant of, or other person authorised`
  line `by, the railway administration or ^2[conservator of the port or officer in charge of the air port], and`
  line `be removed from the place where he is arrested and conveyed as soon as conveniently may be`
  line `before a Magistrate.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s, 15, ibid., for "ship or boat" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "conservator of the port" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (48885)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 24
  title `Saving and power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48885&sectionno=14&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Saving and power to exempt.--(1) Nothing in this Act, except sections 8,9 and 9A shall apply`
  line `to the manufacture, possession, use, transport or importation of any explosive--`
  line
  line `(a) by any of the ^2[Armed Forces of the Union, and ordnance factories or other establishments of`
  line `such Forces) in accordance with rules or regulations made by ^3*** the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) by any person employed under ^4[the Central Government or under a State Government] in`
  line `execution of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may by notification in the Official Gazette exempt, absolutely or subject`
  line `to any such conditions as it may think fit to impose, ^5[any explosive and any person or class of`
  line `persons from all or any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 18 of 1945, s. 4, for section 14.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 16, for "Indian Forces" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `3. The words "His Majesty's Government in the United Kingdom or" omitted by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "any Government in British India"`
  line .
  line `5. Subs. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 16, for certain words (w.e.f. 2-2-1983)`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (48886)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 25
  title `Saving of Arms Act, 1959.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48886&sectionno=15&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall affect the provisions of`
  line `the ^1[Arms Act, 1959 (4 of 1959)]:`
  line
  line `Provided that an authority granting a license under th is Act for the manufacture,`
  line `possession, sale, transport or importation of an explosive may, if empowered in this`
  line `behalf by the rules under which the license is granted, direct by an order written on the`
  line `license that it shall have the effect of a like license granted under the said ^2*** Arms`
  line `(4 of 1959) Act, 1959.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for "Indian Arms Act, 1878" (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  line
  line `2. The word "Indian" omitted by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (48887)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 26
  title `Saving as to liability under other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48887&sectionno=16&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act or the rules under`
  line `this Act shall prevent any person from being prosecuted unde r any other law for any`
  line `act or omission which constitutes an offence against this Act or those rules, or from`
  line `being liable under that other law to any other or higher punishment or penalty than that`
  line `provided by this Act or those rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person shall not be punished twice for the same offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (48888)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 27
  title `Extension of definition of “explosive” to other explosive substances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48888&sectionno=17&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Central Government may, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare that any substance which appears to the Central Government to be specially`
  line `dangerous to life or property, by reason either of its explosive properties or of any`
  line `process in the manufacture thereof being liable to explosion, shall be deemed to be an`
  line `explosive within the meaning of this Act; and the provisions of this Act (subject to such`
  line `exceptions, limitations and restrictions as may be specified in the notification) shall`
  line `accordingly extend to that substance in like manner as if it were included in the`
  line `definition of the term "explosive" in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (48889)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to delegate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-3-1983).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48889&sectionno=17A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Power to delegate.--The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, direct that any power or function which may be exercised or`
  line `performed by it under this Act other than the power under sections 5, 6, 6A, 14 and 17`
  line `may, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as it may`
  line `specify in the notification, be exercised or performed also by--`
  line
  line `(a) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government, or`
  line
  line `(b) such State Government or such officer or authority subordinate to the State`
  line Government.]
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (48890)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 29
  title `Procedure for making, publication and confirmation of rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845&sectionId=48890&sectionno=18&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_188404_1523272950845
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) An`
  line `authority making rules under this Act shall before making the rules, publish a draft of`
  line `the proposed rules for the information of persons likely to be affected thereby.`
  line
  line `(2) The publication shall be made in such manner as th e Central Government, from`
  line `time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette prescribes.`
  line
  line `(3) There shall be published with the draft a notice specifying a date at or after`
  line `which the draft will be taken into consideration.`
  line
  line `(4) The authority making the rules shall receive and consider any objection or`
  line `suggestion which may be made by any person with respect to the draft before the da te`
  line `so specified.`
  line
  line `(5) A rule made under this Act shall not take effect ^1*** until it has been`
  line `published in the Official Gazette ^2***`
  line
  line `(6) The publication in the Official Gazette of a rule purporting to be made under`
  line `this Act shall be conclusive evidence that it has been duly made, and, if it, requires sanction, that it has`
  line `been duly sanctioned.`
  line
  line `(7) All powers to make rules conferred by this Act may he exercised from time to time as`
  line `occasion requires.`
  line
  line `^3[(8) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making`
  line `any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however,`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "if it is made by the Governor-General in Council" omitted by the A.O.1937.`
  line
  line `2. The words "and if it is made by the Local Government until it has been published in the local Official`
  line `Gazette" omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `3.Ins. by Act 32 of 1978, s. 19 (w.e.f. 2 -3-1983).`
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
